    raw2019

    raw2019.Rd

    This is the imported raw version of the 2019 YRBS Data. This data set monitors priority health risk behaviors that contribute markedly to the leading causes of death, disability, and social problems among youth and adults in the United States. These behaviors, often include:

    #' Please refer to the documentation provided in the 2019 National YRBS Data Users Guide.

    These broad categories include:

    • Behaviors that contribute to unintentional injuries and violence

    • Sexual behaviors that contribute to unintended pregnancy and sexually transmitted diseases, including HIV infection

    • Alcohol and other drug use

    • Tobacco use

    • Unhealthy dietary behaviors

    • Inadequate physical activity

    data(raw2019)

    Format

    A tibble with 13,677 and 235 variables

    Details

    Youth Risk Behavior Surveillance System 2019
